Note:
============================================================================
TIME AND SCHEDULING SYSCALLS
============================================================================
clock_gettime is the POSIX time API supported by Linux, Darwin, and all
BSDs. Windows uses GetSystemTimePreciseAsFileTime under the hood; its
platform/syscall.runa exposes SYS_CLOCK_GETTIME as a synthetic number
that the WindowsX86_64 syscall_3 dispatcher recognizes and routes to
the Win32 timer API.
sched_getaffinity is Linux/BSD-specific. Darwin uses thread_policy_set
(via Mach), Windows uses SetThreadAffinityMask. Platforms without
native affinity should return their nominal CPU count.
:End Note

